{"name": "pydantic-sweep", "metadata": {"name": "pydantic-sweep", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL 2.0)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Typing :: Typed"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://berkenkamp.me/pydantic_sweep", "dependencies": ["more-itertools", "pydantic"], "summary": "Programmatic parameter sweeps for pydantic.", "upload_time": 1735493645}, "documentation": ["# pydantic-sweep\n\n`pydantic_sweep` is a library to programmatically, safely and flexibly define \ncomplex parameter sweeps over `pydantic` models in Python. \n\n![PyPI - Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pydantic-sweep)\n![Static Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10%20%7C%203.11%20%7C%203.12%20%7C%203.13-blue)\n![GitHub branch check runs](https://img.shields.io/github/check-runs/befelix/pydantic_sweep/main)\n![GitHub License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/befelix/pydantic_sweep)\n\n**Highlights**:\n- Specify parameter sweeps in Python\n- Flexibility: specify complex parameter combinations by chaining simple operations\n- Safety checks for parameter combinations (get meaningful errors early)\n- `pydantic` field validation\n\nFor example, the following code will instantiate models with `(x=5, y=1)` and \n(`x=6, y=2)` and try each of those with seed values of `seed=43` and `seed=44`, \nleading to four different configurations:\n\n```python\nimport pydantic_sweep as ps\n\nclass Model(ps.BaseModel):\n    seed: int = 42\n    x: int = 5\n    y: int\n\nmodels = ps.initialize(\n    Model, \n    ps.config_product(\n        ps.field(\"seed\", [43, 44]),\n        ps.config_zip(\n            ps.field(\"x\", [ps.DefaultValue, 6]),\n            ps.field(\"y\", [1, 2]),\n        )\n    )\n)\n\n# The code above is equivalent to\nmodels = [\n    Model(seed=43, x=5, y=1), \n    Model(seed=43, x=6, y=2), \n    Model(seed=44, x=5, y=1), \n    Model(seed=44, x=6, y=2),\n]\n```\n\nTo learn mode about the full capabilities of the library visit the\n[documentation page](https://berkenkamp.me/pydantic_sweep/).\n\n## Installation\n\nYou can install the library by checking out the repo and running\n\n```bash\npip install 'pydantic_sweep'\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils._path_to_str", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "p", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Path", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Explanation:", "^ - Matches the start of the string.", "We first match a valid key, followed by dot-seperated valid keys", "$ - Matches the end of the string."]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.normalize_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Path", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "check_keys", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "StrictPath", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.StrictPath", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Normalize a path to a tuple of strings.\n\n# Parameters\n\npath :\n\n: The path to be normalized.\n\ncheck_keys :\n\n: If `True`, also check each individual key in a tuple path.\n"]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Path", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "d", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the value of a nested dict at a certain path."]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_replace", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Path", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "d", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "inplace", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Replace the value of a nested dict at a certain path (out of place)."]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_at", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Path", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Return nested dictionary with the value at path."]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_from_items", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "items", "type": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.abc.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Path", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Convert paths and values (items) to a nested dictionary.\n\nPaths are assumed as single dot-separated strings."]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_items", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Path", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "d", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Iterator", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.abc.Iterator", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "StrictPath", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.StrictPath", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["Yield paths and leaf values of a nested dictionary.\n\n```pycon\n>>> list(nested_dict_items(dict(a=dict(b=3), c=2)))\n[(('a', 'b'), 3), (('c',), 2)]\n```\n"]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.merge_nested_dicts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*dicts", "type": {"name": "Config", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Config", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "overwrite", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Config", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep.types.Config", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Merge multiple Config dictionaries into a single one.\n\nThis function includes error checking for duplicate keys and accidental overwriting\nof subtrees in the nested configuration objects.\n\n```pycon\n>>> merge_nested_dicts(dict(a=dict(b=2)), dict(c=3))\n{'a': {'b': 2}, 'c': 3}\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> merge_nested_dicts(dict(a=dict(b=2)), dict(a=5), overwrite=True)\n{'a': 5}\n```\n"]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.random_seeds", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "num", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "upper", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Generate unique random values within a certain range.\n\nThis is useful in scenarios where we don't want to hard-code a random seed,\nbut also need reproducibility by setting a seed. Sampling the random seed is a\ngood compromise there.\n\nParameters\n----------\nnum :\n    The number of random seeds to generate.\nupper:\n    A non-inclusive upper bound on the maximum seed to generate.\n\nReturns\n-------\nlist[int]:\n    A list of integer seeds."]}], "variables": [{"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.valid_key_pattern", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils._STR_PATH_PATTERN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils._STR_KEY_PATTERN", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.merge_nested_dicts", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._utils.merge_nested_dicts", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_at", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_at", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_from_items", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_from_items", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_get", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_get", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_replace", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._utils.nested_dict_replace", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.normalize_path", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._utils.normalize_path", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep._utils.random_seeds", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._utils.random_seeds", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pydantic_sweep.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._version.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep.BaseModel", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._model.BaseModel", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep.check_model", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._model.check_model", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep.config_chain", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._model.config_chain", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep.config_combine", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._model.config_combine", "project": null}}, {"name": "pydantic_sweep.config_product", "xref": {"fqname": "pydantic_sweep._model.config_product", "